taipo
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number: 5
Definition:a children's nickname, or abusive epithet, for an unattractive Maori


Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1935 Havelock Mungamunga taipo (or `tarpot'), probably from mangamanga. black. [Note that [wi:rou] also used in a similar context at that time and place: ?Maori <i>whiro</i> 1. evil, bad 2. the proper name of a malevolent atua, personification of evil, and of darkness and of death.]
