Author:  PARK
Vol / Page:  127
Edition:
Quote:  ...shaking showers of white quince blossom down upon herself, she yelled, <i>`Maunga manga taipo!'</i> at Mauri in an unreasoning, provocative impudence, but he did not mind being called a black devil and cuffed good-naturedly at her head with a big brown paw.
Notes:

Date:  0/7/1954
Source:  Numbers
Author:
Vol / Page:  1/4
Edition:
Quote:  ... the happiest days of our lives. Young white gods yelling <i>mangumangu taipo!</i> without knowing what it meant, only that it was something to be yelled at the Maori kids in the swamps on Sunday afternoon. <i>Mangumangu taipo</i>, nigger-man devils! And it didn't much matter that you yourself weren't a Maori, ...
Notes:  (Mincher)
